Introduction

KiiiKiii is a five-member South Korean girl group under Starship Entertainment.

On February 10, 2025, Starship Entertainment opened multiples SNS accounts teasing the group and revealing its name to be "KiiiKiii". On their Instagram account, a post showed the members names to be Sumin, Subin, Haum, Kya, and Jiyu. However, at the end of the "I DO ME" MV, the names were Sui, Haum, Jiyu, Leesol, and Kya, teasing stage names for two of the members.

KiiiKiii released the MV for "I DO ME", the title track of their debut EP, "UNCUT GEM", as a pre-release on February 16, 2025. A few days later, on February 23, they dropped the MV for the bside "DEBUT SONG". The group finally made their debut on March 24, 2025, with the release of their EP as well as an MV for their promoted bside "BTG".

KiiiKiii announced their fandom name to be "TiiiKiii" on April 24, 2025. The name is derived from "Tiki Taka", and means that KiiiKiii and their fans will always be a good match and in harmony with each other.
